#3rd one
# Start Jenkins Server
java -jar jenkins.war --httpPort=8080

# Open Jenkins in browser
http://localhost:8080

# Start ngrok to expose Jenkins server
ngrok http 8080

# Copy the HTTPS forwarding URL from ngrok
# Example:
https://abcd1234.ngrok.io

# Create Jenkins Project (in Jenkins UI)
Jenkins Dashboard → New Item → Enter Project Name → Select Freestyle Project → OK

# Connect GitHub Repository
Source Code Management → Git
Repository URL: https://github.com/KhushiJigali/frst.git

# Enable Webhook Trigger
Build Triggers → Select "GitHub hook trigger for GITScm polling"

# Configure Webhook in GitHub
Repository → Settings → Webhooks → Add Webhook

Payload URL:
https://abcd1234.ngrok.io/github-webhook/

Content Type:
application/json

Event Trigger:
Just the push event

# Save Webhook

# Now push code to trigger Jenkins build
git add .
git commit -m "Trigger Jenkins Build"
git push origin master

